-- OTP Bank Climbs for First Time in Seven Days on Stimulus Bets
-- B y   A n d r a s   G e r g e l y
-- 2012-07-13T12:30:49Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-13/otp-bank-climbs-for-first-time-in-seven-days-on-stimulus-bets.html
OTP Bank Nyrt. (OTP) , Hungary’s largest
lender, snapped six days of declines as speculation that China
will add to stimulus for the world’s second-largest economy
boosted demand for riskier assets.  The stock climbed 0.9 percent to 3,438 forint by 2:17 p.m.
in Budapest, paring its loss this week to 2.9 percent. The
benchmark BUX equity index rose 0.2 percent.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andras Gergely in Budapest at 
 agergely@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
